<reference id="api_iaudioframeobserver_getrecordaudioparams">
    <title><ph keyref="getRecordAudioParams"/></title>
    <shortdesc id="short"><ph id="shortdesc" props="android">Sets the audio format for the <xref keyref="onRecordAudioFrame"/> callback.</ph></shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <metadata>
            <keywords>
                <indexterm keyref="getRecordAudioParams"/>
            </keywords>
        </metadata>
    </prolog>
    <refbody>
        <section id="prototype">
            <p outputclass="codeblock">
                <codeblock props="android" outputclass="language-java">@CalledByNative public abstract AudioParams getRecordAudioParams();</codeblock>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="detailed_desc" deliveryTarget="details" otherprops="no-title">
            <p props="android">After calling <xref keyref="registerAudioFrameObserver"/> to register the callback, the SDK triggers this callback. You can set the audio format in the return value of this callback.</p>
            <note props="android">The SDK calculates the sampling interval and triggers the <xref keyref="onRecordAudioFrame"/> callback based on the <xref keyref="AudioParams"/> you set in the return value. Sampling interval (seconds) = <codeph>samplePerCall</codeph> / (<codeph>sampleRate</codeph> × <codeph>channel</codeph>). Make sure the sampling interval is ≥ 0.01 seconds.</note>
        </section>
        <section id="return_values" props="android">
            <title>Return Values</title>
            <p props="android">If the method call succeeds, returns an <xref keyref="AudioParams"/> object.</p>
        </section>
    </refbody>
</reference>